Package interfaces

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    I_Copiable<T>
    Describes the behavior of an object to copy the fields of another object (of the same type).
    I_Fileable
    Describes the behavior of an object to be easily converted to and from a string.
    I_FileReader
    Describes the behavior of opening and reading files.
    I_FileWriter
    Describes the behavior of writing to and modifying files.
    I_HasChanged
    Objects that implement this correctly have a simplified way of determining whether one object is equal to another.
    I_InitializeLater
    Interface that describes the ability for an object to be set after the scene has been set.
